metadata.name: Helio_Motion #50
metadata.description:
Original piece by Ismahelio. p5js.

Infinite combinations of minimal, cubist like, glitch 3d-2dimensional illustrations
There is a huge variation in color combinations, some of them are inspired by digital and physical artists.
Chances to get a specific color palette are:
 
1 % Locomotion
3 % Lionel Radisson
6 % Acidquiat
10 % Saura
10 % Wong
15 % NFT Biker
25 % CMYK
30 % Ganbrood

There's also rarity in the number of shapes and the piece sizes: S, M, L, and XL.

The piece is interactive. Depending on the number of views, the animation will change if you click on the screen. If the number of views is 1, then it won't change!

metadata.name: Annum #8418
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: wallabye pop #58
metadata.description:
digital wallaby in its new blockchain environment made of Tezos API data

there are currently 3 species of wallaby classed as extinct in NSW, Australia - let's protect the remaining species so living on the blockchain is not their future

in this version, blockchain api data (text) is displayed as blocks, hidden / encoded in the drawing

some iterations will show close-up views of the wallaby, as lines/mesh, to see different perspectives of the species and their view in their new digital habitat


::: experimental p5.js, WEBGL API drawing
::: ** may be very slow or unresponsive on iOS browsers/devices **
::: blockchain API data is read from a file, not requested dynamically, to maintain a self-contained drawing for fxhash platform
::: previews may differ slightly to main image
::: API data as digital landscape / architecture / habitat
::: part of my specture series
::: 18/11/2022
::: fxhashTurnsOne

metadata.name: Tunnels #718
metadata.description:
"Tunnels" explores using generative backgrounds to lead a field of isometric shapes. How the foreground and background interact varies wildly from generation to generation. "Tunnels" can seem to have an exit and sometimes seem to lead into nowhere.

Royalties Splits:
50% Donation to minter

Features:
Four different sizes: 9x16, 11x14", 12x18", 12x12"
Portrait or landscape orientation
~500 color pallets, one black and white, one cyan, magenta, yellow and black, and the rest from Jam3/nice-color-palettes.

Dependencies:
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes
@liamegan1/fxhash-helpers
@altesc/stdio

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size (see features for dimensions)

License: CC-BY

Please find me on Twitter and Instagram at @natenolting.

metadata.name: Lime Brass Hyacinth #329
metadata.description: "Lime Brass Hyacinth" is a p5.js project where isometric shapes are placed and have their size and color adjusted based on an underlying grid of gradients. Each form is derived from the lightness or darkness of a particular pixel in the underlying grid. Many renders remind me of cityscapes with buildings, roads, and bridges.
